Title: How to jump start a 2010 Honda Insight

Lines.Text: make sure that both cars are turned off .
pop open the hood of the insight by pulling the lever located here :

Steps.Text_raw: Make sure that both cars are turned off. Pop open the hood of the Insight by pulling the lever located here:

Lines.Text: open the hood by reaching under the hood ( in the front and center ) and pulling the lever .

Steps.Text_raw: Open the hood by reaching under the hood (in the front and center) and pulling the lever.

Lines.Text: lock open the hood by grabbing the rod and inserting it into the hole on the under side of the hood .

Steps.Text_raw: Lock open the hood by grabbing the rod and inserting it into the hole on the under side of the hood.

Lines.Text: open the hood of the charged car , and lock it up into place ( with rod if necessary ) .
spring-action rod

Steps.Text_raw: Open the hood of the charged car, and lock it up into place (with rod if necessary). Spring-action rod

Lines.Text: grab your jumper cables .
locate the battery in the dead-battery car and the charged-battery car .
the battery always has a big red plastic part that will indicate the positive terminal .

Steps.Text_raw: Locate the battery in the dead-battery car and the charged-battery car. The battery always has a big red plastic part that will indicate the positive terminal.

Lines.Text: warning ! do not let the leads touch each other or any other metal !
attach the red lead to the '''charged car's''' battery where the positive ( red ) terminal is .

Steps.Text_raw: WARNING! DO NOT LET THE LEADS TOUCH EACH OTHER OR ANY OTHER METAL! Attach the RED lead to the '''charged car's''' battery where the positive (RED) terminal is.

Lines.Text: attach the other red lead to the positive ( red ) terminal of the '''dead car's''' battery .

Steps.Text_raw: Attach the other RED lead to the positive (RED) terminal of the '''dead car's''' battery.

Lines.Text: attach the black lead to the '''charged car's''' battery where the negative terminal is .

Steps.Text_raw: Attach the BLACK lead to the '''charged car's''' battery where the negative terminal is.

Lines.Text: attach the other black lead to the grounding strap located here :
do not connect the black lead to any other part of the car .

Steps.Text_raw: Attach the other BLACK lead to the grounding strap located here: Do not connect the black lead to any other part of the car.

Lines.Text: start the engine of the '''charged car''' and let the engine run for ++1-2 minutes . ++

Steps.Text_raw: Start the engine of the '''charged car''' and let the engine run for ++1-2 minutes.++

Lines.Text: start the engine of the '''dead car''' and let it run for ++2-3 minutes . ++
note : if your insight does not start at this point , let the battery charge for a few more minutes .

Steps.Text_raw: Start the engine of the '''dead car''' and let it run for ++2-3 minutes.++ NOTE: If your Insight does not start at this point, let the battery charge for a few more minutes.

Lines.Text: after the insight has successfully started and has been running for a ++few minutes++ , remove leads in reverse order from attachment .
warning : do not let the leads touch each other or any other metal !

Steps.Text_raw: After the Insight has successfully started and has been running for a ++few minutes++, remove leads in reverse order from attachment. WARNING: DO NOT LET THE LEADS TOUCH EACH OTHER OR ANY OTHER METAL!

Lines.Text: drive the insight for at least ++30 minutes ++before turning it off again to ensure a full charge for your battery .
note : you may also simply let the engine run for 30 minutes rather than driving .

Steps.Text_raw: Drive the Insight for at least ++30 minutes ++before turning it off again to ensure a full charge for your battery. NOTE: You may also simply let the engine run for 30 minutes rather than driving.
